               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gәbrä ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week” (fols. 2ra-248va) &#xD;
I-1) Introduction (fols. 2ra-4vb) &#xD;
I-2) Eve of Palm Sunday (fols. 4vb-7vb) &#xD;
I-3) Palm Sunday (fols. 8ra-18rb) &#xD;
I-4) Monday (fols. 18rb-46vb) &#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 18rb-23va) &#xD;
- Day hours (fols. 23va-46vb) &#xD;
I-5) Tuesday (fols. 46vb-70ra) &#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 46vb-51ra) &#xD;
- Day hours (fols. 51ra-70ra) &#xD;
I-6) Wednesday (fols. 70ra-87rb) &#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 70ra-73rb) &#xD;
- Day hours (fols. 73rb-87rb) &#xD;
I-7) Thursday (fols. 87rb-114vb) &#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 87rb-91rb) &#xD;
- Day hours (fols. 91rb-114vb) &#xD;
I-8) Friday (fols. 115ra-180va) &#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 115ra-130ra) &#xD;
- Day hours (fols. 130ra-180va), including: Homily by Jacob of Serug on Abraham (fols. 148vb-155va) &#xD;
I-9) Saturday (fols. 180va-205rb)&#xD;
- Night hours (fols. 180va-196va)&#xD;
- Mass (fols. 196va-205rb), including: Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt “Teaching of Mysteries” (fols. 203vb-205rb)&#xD;
I-10) Maṣḥafa dorho “Book of the Cock” (fols. 205va-219ra)&#xD;
I-11) Homilies on Passion of Christ&#xD;
- Homily by Ephrem on Passion of Our Lord and on the thief on the right hand (fols. 219ra-222rb) &#xD;
- Homily by Cyriacus of Behnesa [Lāḥā Māryām “Lamentation of Mary”] (fols. 222rb-248va).</summary>
